</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA13d258n1-ptr" id="PJA13d258n1">1</a>

   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> included the text of Fitzherberts 24 July commission in his letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-13-02-0152" class="document">18 Aug.</a> to Livingston, above, and Oswalds 25 July commission in his letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-13-02-0201" class="document">16 Sept.</a> (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Papers of the Continental Congress. Originals in the National Archives: Record Group 360. Microfilm edition in 204 reels. Usually cited in the present work from the microfilms, but according to the original series and volume numbering devised in the State Department in the early 19th century; for example, PCC, No. 93, III, i.e. the third volume of series 93.&lt;/expan&gt; ]">PCC</span>, No. 84, IV, f. 169172). For the text of Oswalds commission see <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Revolutionary Diplomatic Correspondence of the United States&lt;/i&gt;, ed. Francis Wharton, Washington, D.C., 1889; 6 vols. ]">Wharton, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Dipl. Corr. Amer. Rev.</span></span>, 5:613614. <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> included the 16 Sept. letter among those that he sent to the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Boston Patriot</span>, where it appeared on 29 June 1811. But see Oswalds second commission, dated <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-13-02-0209" class="document">[<ins title="editorial addition or explanation" class="ed">21 Sept.</ins>]</a>, below.</p>

